      "writtenOn": "2020-07-21T22:27:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This looks good to me, but I want to fire off a few trybots before we land.\n\nSometimes when we translate things like\n\n   mad(x, y,\n   mad(z, w, k))\n\ninto\n\n    x*y + z*w + k\n\nit changes the order of operations, and that\u0027s significant when working with floats.\nI think our CQ + linux-blink-rel will be enough to let us know if any of that matters.\n\nIt certainly won\u0027t matter for speed, and I\u0027d be astonished if it produced anything visibly different, but there are sometimes low-bit changes we should be aware of (to rebaseline goldens, etc).",
      "revId": "7f2e99640c6b9e57890534970a8b493810933c0b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
